{"title_page": "'Till I Collapse", "text_new": "{{Infobox song|name='Till I Collapse|cover=|alt=|type=|artist=[[Eminem]] featuring [[Nate Dogg]]|album=[[The Eminem Show]]|released=May 26, 2002|format=|recorded=2001|studio=|venue=|genre=|length=4:58|label={{hlist|[[Aftermath Entertainment|Aftermath]]|[[Shady Records|Shady]]|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]}}|writer={{hlist|[[Eminem|Marshall Mathers]]|[[Nathaniel Hale]]|[[Luis Resto (musician)|Luis Resto]]}}|producer=Eminem|misc={{External music video|{{YouTube|ytQ5CYE1VZw|\"'Till I Collapse\"}}}}}}\"'''Till I Collapse'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Eminem]], released from his fourth [[studio album]], ''[[The Eminem Show]]'', in 2002. It is the 18th track on the album, and features American rapper [[Nate Dogg]] performing the [[hook (music)|hook]]. Despite never being released as a single, the song has managed to chart numerous times worldwide.\n\n== Background ==\n\nAlthough it has never been released as a single, it has charted on a few occasions when other Eminem albums have been released.<ref name=\"zobbel\"/> In 2012 it was certified [[Music recording sales certification|double-platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] for digital sales of 2,000,000 copies in the United States.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Eminem&format=ALBUM&go=Search&perPage=50 riaa.com]  {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HcOuKzMn?url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Eminem&format=ALBUM&go=Search&perPage=50 |date=June 24, 2013 }}</ref> In 2018 it was certified quintuple-platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America for digital sales of 5,000,000 copies in the United States.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=eminem#search_section RIAA - Gold & Platinum Searchable Database - May 09, 2014]  {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CPbPfOi3?url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?artist=Eminem |date=November 24, 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nWhen Eminem's single \"[[Shake That]]\" (also featuring Nate Dogg) was released in 2006, several Eminem songs re-charted that same week, including \"'Till I Collapse\". It charted in the [[United Kingdom]] at number 192 on 15 April 2006.<ref name=\"zobbel\">[http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_E.HTM \"Chart Log UK: E-40 - E-Z Rollers\"]. zobbel.de. Retrieved 3 January 2011. {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Gfy0Ug5r?url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_E.HTM |date=May 17, 2013 }}</ref> In 2008, it appeared in HBO's Oscar de la Hoya \u2013 Manny Pacquiao 24/7.\n\nIn 2009, it was used in an advert for the then-upcoming game ''[[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2]]''. It raised digital download sales of the song worldwide considerably,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.fitplanapp.com/the-20-greatest-workout-songs-of-all-time/|title=''Most Popular Workout Songs of All Time on Spotify''|last=|first=|date=1 March 2019|work=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2019-03-01}}{{cbignore}}</ref> but in [[United Kingdom|Britain]] the song sold so many copies after the advert aired that it re-charted that week (21 November 2009) at number 73, a new peak. [[Shane Mosley]] used this song as an entrance theme with his bout with [[Floyd Mayweather]] as did [[Shane Carwin]] for his bout against [[Junior dos Santos]]. Major League Baseball pitcher [[Jesse Litsch]] used the song as his entrance music during the [[2011 Major League Baseball season|2011]] season.<ref name=\"Jays Dome\">[http://netknives.com/ \"Net knives\"]. Walkup Music. Retrieved 29 September 2011.</ref> The song has also been used in the credits of the Season 8 premiere of ''[[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|Entourage]]''. It was also used in September 2011 in the trailer and soundtrack for the film ''[[Real Steel]]'', and in trailers and TV spots for the [[Oliver Stone]]-directed film ''[[Savages (2012 film)|Savages]]''. During the 2013\u201314 [[NBA]] season, the song was used during the [[Brooklyn Nets]]' team introductions.\n\n==Chart positions==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2006\u201318)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canadian [[Canadian Digital Songs|Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22%27Till%20I%20Collapse%22&f[1]=ts_chart_artistname%3AEminem%20Featuring%20Nate%20Dogg&refine=1&solrsort=sort_label%3Aasc|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 28, 2018|title=Eminem Featuring Nate Dogg - 'Till I Collapse|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180428103948/https://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=ss_chart_search_title:%22'Till%20I%20Collapse%22&f%5B1%5D=ts_chart_artistname:Eminem%20Featuring%20Nate%20Dogg&refine=1&solrsort=sort_label:asc|archivedate=April 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|30\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Irish Singles Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irma.ie/aucharts.asp |publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]] |accessdate=21 September 2012 |archivedate=21 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AqGSJi0u?url=http://www.irma.ie/aucharts.asp |title=Irish Charts - Week ending 20th September 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n|77\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakdigital|100|year=2016|week=41|accessdate=October 17, 2016|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Sweden Heatseekers ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=215&dfom=20171110|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|language=Swedish|accessdate=April 28, 2018|title=Veckolista Heatseeker - Vecka 46, 17 november 2017}}</ref>\n|10\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|73|artist=Eminem|song=Till I Collapse|accessdate=April 28, 2018|rowheader=true|date=20091115}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddigitalsongs|35|artist=Eminem|song=Till I Collapse|accessdate=April 28, 2018|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Denmark|artist=Eminem|title=Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=2002|certyear=2013|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifpi.dk/?q=content/eminem-till-i-collapse|publisher=IFPI Denmark|title=Eminem \u2013 Till I Collapse|accessdate=May 12, 2013|date=March 15, 2013|language=Danish}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|artist=Eminem|title=Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=2002|certyear=2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Italy|artist=Eminem|title='Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Platinum|number=2|relyear=2002|certyear=2019|accessdate=October 21, 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|artist=Eminem|title='Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Platinum|relyear=2002|certyear=2018|id=13426-438-1|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|artist=Eminem|title='Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Platinum|number=5|relyear=2002|certyear=2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true|nosales=true}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|eminem|till-i-collapse}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Eminem singles}}\n{{Nate Dogg}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Till I Collapse}}\n[[Category:2002 songs]]\n[[Category:Eminem songs]]\n[[Category:Nate Dogg songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Eminem]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Luis Resto (musician)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Nate Dogg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song|name='Till I Collapse|cover=|alt=|type=|artist=[[Eminem]] featuring [[Nate Dogg]]|album=[[The Eminem Show]]|released=May 26, 2002|format=|recorded=2001|studio=|venue=|genre=|length=4:58|label={{hlist|[[Aftermath Entertainment|Aftermath]]|[[Shady Records|Shady]]|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]}}|writer={{hlist|[[Eminem|Marshall Mathers]]|[[Nathaniel Hale]]|[[Luis Resto (musician)|Luis Resto]]}}|producer=Eminem|misc={{External music video|{{YouTube|ytQ5CYE1VZw|\"'Till I Collapse\"}}}}}}\"'''Till I Collapse'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Eminem]], released from his fourth [[studio album]], ''[[The Eminem Show]]'', in 2002. It is the 18th track on the album, and features American rapper [[Nate Dogg]] performing the [[hook (music)|hook]]. Despite never being released as a single, the song has managed to chart numerous times worldwide.\n\n== Background ==\n\nAlthough it has never been released as a single, it has charted on a few occasions when other Eminem albums have been released.<ref name=\"zobbel\"/> In 2012 it was certified [[Music recording sales certification|double-platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] for digital sales of 2,000,000 copies in the United States.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Eminem&format=ALBUM&go=Search&perPage=50 riaa.com]  {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HcOuKzMn?url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Eminem&format=ALBUM&go=Search&perPage=50 |date=June 24, 2013 }}</ref> In 2018 it was certified quintuple-platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America for digital sales of 5,000,000 copies in the United States.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=eminem#search_section RIAA - Gold & Platinum Searchable Database - May 09, 2014]  {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CPbPfOi3?url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?artist=Eminem |date=November 24, 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nWhen Eminem's single \"[[Shake That]]\" (also featuring Nate Dogg) was released in 2006, several Eminem songs re-charted that same week, including \"'Till I Collapse\". It charted in the [[United Kingdom]] at number 192 on 15 April 2006.<ref name=\"zobbel\">[http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_E.HTM \"Chart Log UK: E-40 - E-Z Rollers\"]. zobbel.de. Retrieved 3 January 2011. {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Gfy0Ug5r?url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_E.HTM |date=May 17, 2013 }}</ref> In 2008, it appeared in HBO's Oscar de la Hoya \u2013 Manny Pacquiao 24/7.\n\nIn 2009, it was used in an advert for the then-upcoming game ''[[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2]]''. It raised digital download sales of the song worldwide considerably,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8492169/eminem-kanye-west-spotify-most-popular-workout-songs |title=''Most Popular Workout Songs of All Time on Spotify'' |work=Billboard |date=1 March 2019 |accessdate=2019-03-01 }}{{dead link|date=February 2017}}{{cbignore}}</ref> but in [[United Kingdom|Britain]] the song sold so many copies after the advert aired that it re-charted that week (21 November 2009) at number 73, a new peak. [[Shane Mosley]] used this song as an entrance theme with his bout with [[Floyd Mayweather]] as did [[Shane Carwin]] for his bout against [[Junior dos Santos]]. Major League Baseball pitcher [[Jesse Litsch]] used the song as his entrance music during the [[2011 Major League Baseball season|2011]] season.<ref name=\"Jays Dome\">[http://netknives.com/ \"Net knives\"]. Walkup Music. Retrieved 29 September 2011.</ref> The song has also been used in the credits of the Season 8 premiere of ''[[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|Entourage]]''. It was also used in September 2011 in the trailer and soundtrack for the film ''[[Real Steel]]'', and in trailers and TV spots for the [[Oliver Stone]]-directed film ''[[Savages (2012 film)|Savages]]''. During the 2013\u201314 [[NBA]] season, the song was used during the [[Brooklyn Nets]]' team introductions.\n\n==Chart positions==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2006\u201318)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canadian [[Canadian Digital Songs|Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22%27Till%20I%20Collapse%22&f[1]=ts_chart_artistname%3AEminem%20Featuring%20Nate%20Dogg&refine=1&solrsort=sort_label%3Aasc|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 28, 2018|title=Eminem Featuring Nate Dogg - 'Till I Collapse|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180428103948/https://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=ss_chart_search_title:%22'Till%20I%20Collapse%22&f%5B1%5D=ts_chart_artistname:Eminem%20Featuring%20Nate%20Dogg&refine=1&solrsort=sort_label:asc|archivedate=April 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|30\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Irish Singles Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irma.ie/aucharts.asp |publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]] |accessdate=21 September 2012 |archivedate=21 September 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AqGSJi0u?url=http://www.irma.ie/aucharts.asp |title=Irish Charts - Week ending 20th September 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n|77\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakdigital|100|year=2016|week=41|accessdate=October 17, 2016|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Sweden Heatseekers ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=215&dfom=20171110|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|language=Swedish|accessdate=April 28, 2018|title=Veckolista Heatseeker - Vecka 46, 17 november 2017}}</ref>\n|10\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|73|artist=Eminem|song=Till I Collapse|accessdate=April 28, 2018|rowheader=true|date=20091115}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddigitalsongs|35|artist=Eminem|song=Till I Collapse|accessdate=April 28, 2018|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Denmark|artist=Eminem|title=Till I Collapse|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=2002|certyear=2013|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifpi.dk/?q=content/eminem-till-i-collapse|publisher=IFP